Text.Value: With trained worgs on your scent? Not likely.
I've seen what the goblins can do to a vulnerable caravan, so I'm not as confident.
No, I won't waste my time.
Excellent! And since I ain't one to leave a debt unpaid, that means we're destined to meet in Baldur's Gate.
Even if the light is just as bleak as everything else, and...
...you know what? Never mind. It wasn't that funny.
Sure, it's a bet. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
How are you going to take my gold if you're dead?
It is not funny.
Thanks for your helpful feedback, but I think we're done here.
We need to move. No point staying here - twiddling our thumbs.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Tense, looking around with a frown.
EditorData.NodeContext: Tense and nervous but trying to hide it.

Text.Value: Come on. What do you say?
If you survived the Hells, you'll survive this.
Try not to keel over with the first blade drawn.
A defeat is a defeat. There is no glory in that.
Not with that attitude. Fight and win!
No, I - it's a joke.
But if you're so sure we will, why not put a little gold on the line?
Thanks. You're all right.
Oh, I see. Quite amusing.
Plenty of us fell to monsters already. I don't see the rest of us lasting long out there.
I'm not the wagering type.
All right, you're on. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Who knows, some of us might even make it to Baldur's Gate.
You have an odd sense of humour. This isn't really funny.
After seeing you at the gate, I'm sure you'll last longer than us.
Be safe out there, whatever comes your way.
You are just a ray of sunshine, aren't you?
There's optimism and then there's stupid, hun.
It's taking a really bleak situation and trying to find some light in it.
Well, we came through Avernus. We might not look it, but we're tough.
Explain it.
But if you are, why not put a little gold on the line? ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
No. No, I suppose it isn't.
Looking forward to it.
Will you? I don't see many soldiers.
Maybe you'll catch a glimpse of Baldur's Gate before they cut you down.
Ohh, well aren't you an optimist?
Used to think the goblins'd kill us the second we set foot outside. But after hearing what you did at the gate...
I'd best see you in Baldur's Gate.
I'm sure you're good for it. Just leave the gold on my corpse.
No? Shame, I thought you might enjoy a little fun.
... well, I still think they'll kill us. But at least we can put up a fight.
No, it's not. None of this is funny. But at least this way there's something to play for.
We're tougher than we look. We've survived persecution. Survived Avernus.

Synopsis:
A Tiefling in the druid grove who's keen to banter and joke. She's a bit flirtatious, though there's an undercurrent of fear throughout it all. She's genuinely afraid that she's going to die, and her only coping mechanism is to joke about it - in this case offering to make a bet. She's looking for something to look forward to.
RERECORD NOTES: All lines in that dialogue have been set to rerecord with a few line changes. Overall direction. she needs to a more tongue in cheek humorous delivery.
